    <name>
      <text>Ratio of volumes of similar solids</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The corresponding sides of two <strong>similar</strong> blocks of wood measure {@a@} cm and {@b@} cm. Find the ratio of their volumes.</p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>

<p>
Since the blocks are <strong>similar</strong>, all corresponding lengths scale
by the same factor.
</p>

<p>
The linear scale factor is:
\[
\frac{@b@}{@a@} 
\]
</p>

<p>
For similar solids, volumes scale with the <strong>cube</strong> of the linear
scale factor:
\[
\left({@scale@}\right)^3 = {@ta@}.
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the ratio of the volumes of the smaller block to the larger block is:
\[
1 : {@ta@} = {@ta@}.
\]
</p>
]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
